<br>
Perhaps imagination is something you are born with and then learn to develop!<br>
<br>
Maybe when you go to school you are learning ways to organise more complex uses of your own imagination ( - poor teachers being so wrapped up in getting grades and stuff don't recognise that what they are really doing is enabling others to develop tools - maths, english, etc to organise their imaginings more productively.)<br>
<br>
Consider at one time all the computers and programs we play with were just ideas in someone elses mind - they used maths and language to make them part of reality.<br>
<br>
We are continually provided with better computer systems and software - what about better ways to imagine and organise your own imagination - so that you get what you want?<br>
<br>
<br>
I just had the idea in my mind that you could develop the imagination you were born with to work the way you want it to. Aren't you?<br>
