my drawings have improved a little...except for stuff that uses perspective...I used to be able to churn out cars in 3/4 perspective without worrying about proportion...<br>
I was never really interested in drawing people then but my architecture was good too...<br>
it is coming back slowly...I stopped drawing for a few years...<br>
there was a time before I stopped though that people would come to me and have them draw stuff...it was me and another kid...and you either went to me or him...<br>
But I needed to work on school more...and the getting up early and waiting in shitty weather for a bus that was usually late didn't work well for me...<br>
and having stupid teachers...a lack of friends...<br>
I stopped drawing from about gr.6 till just recently...that might be why I lost it...but even the art courses don't emphasise creativity...they want you to know art history...<br>
I won't get into my down with the current school system rant...but I think big improvements could be made....<br>
