I like a lot of the classical artists...I didn't pay attention enough to learn the periods they were in...but van gogh's work is beautiful...but I won't give you an art history lesson...<br>
I got stuck in a class with a lot of idiots that thought they were all hot @#%$ and got a rise out of making fun of me...In fact that happened both years...I hated it...by the end of that period I was drawing exclusively weird abstract and surreal stuff...the one and only person I got along with that didn't treat me like crap...was the teacher...and I just barely passed both times...it was also an expensive class...<br>
it's not really worth it...I'd stay away from art classes in high school...I didn't learn much...and I could just ask either art teacher and they would bend over backwards to help me...(They were very very nice)...I got more from the art club...that was where the real artists hung out...we painted murals all over the school...(Our school is painted everywhere...it's incredible...)<br>
<br>
Anyway...public education doesn't have the right enviroment for creativity...it's much to harsh...you're always having to cover your back or worry about grades and you cant just relax and expiriment...you have idiots that think it's their right to see your sketches...then judge you on your garbage expiriment drawings...<br>
<br>
If you're one of the smart bunch that is disciplined and can get A's and have free time and not have to worry about rumours and other parents threatening to call the cops on you then they can be as creative as they want...I've never hung around with those people much... <p><pre>
